---
import LibraryStyleLayout from "../../astro/layouts/LibraryStyleLayout.astro";
---

<LibraryStyleLayout>
  <main class="responsive-container">
    <h2>Copyable Snippet</h2>

    <p>
      Use the <code>data-copyable-snippet</code> attribute on any <code
        >&lt;pre&gt;</code
      > element that wraps a <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> block to enable automatic
      copy functionality. A copy button will be injected automatically if not already
      present.
    </p>

    <h3>Example usage:</h3>

    <pre
      data-copyable-snippet><code>&lt;pre data-copyable-snippet&gt;
  &lt;code&gt;
    npm install my-package
  &lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;</code></pre>
    <h3>Rendered snippet:</h3>
    <pre data-copyable-snippet><code>npm install my-package</code></pre>
    <p>
      When the copy button is clicked, the visible text inside the <code
        >&lt;code&gt;</code
      > block (excluding the button itself) will be copied to the clipboard. If the
      Clipboard API is not available (e.g. in insecure contexts), a fallback method
      will be used.
    </p>
  </main>
</LibraryStyleLayout>
